The paper focuses on improving the efficiency of Long Short-Term Memory (LSTM) networks on FPGAs through structured compression techniques. This involves optimizing computation and memory accesses, as well as reducing storage requirements and computational complexity. These topics are relevant to several sub-categories, including cs.AR (Hardware Architecture), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.ET (Embedded Systems).
